Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.15,0:00:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\an8}When I was a child,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.22,0:00:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\an8}I always wondered about the people beyond the valley mist.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.38,0:00:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\an8}They always appeared before the May showers
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.97,0:00:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\an8}and disappeared around when the storms ended.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.14,0:00:48.11,EP Title BG,,0,0,0,,{\fad(2100,2100)\p1\blur1}m 0 0 l 950 0 950 100 0 100
Dialogue: 1,0:00:40.14,0:00:48.11,EP Title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(2100,2100)\be1}The Sound of Footsteps on the Grass
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.21,0:00:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Young master!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.70,0:01:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you'd be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.48,0:01:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The master is calling for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.62,0:01:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a beautiful shade of purple today.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.71,0:01:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It just looks like white mist to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.60,0:01:29.98,Title,,0,0,0,,{\pos(816.19,121.905)\fad(2000,0)\p1\blur1\c&HFFFFFF&\1a&HFF&\3c&HFFFFFF&\3a&H00&\bord10\clip(676,67,956,177)\shad0}m 0 0 l 300 0 300 100 0 100
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.60,0:01:29.98,Title,,0,0,0,,{\pos(814.857,120.906)\fad(2000,0)}Mushishi
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.00,0:01:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure are an odd child.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.90,0:01:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.60,0:01:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It's already that time when those people come, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.45,0:01:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess I should get the storm shutters fixed.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.60,0:01:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it all right, Father, to let them do as they please on our mountain?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.91,0:01:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.05,0:01:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,They won't do anything bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.54,0:01:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard that they've been coming for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.78,0:01:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They chat with the mountain guards and that's about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.02,0:02:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What exactly do they do?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.87,0:02:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know exactly what they do for living,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.73,0:02:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,but they don't seem to request alms.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.50,0:02:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I've never meddled \Nin their business that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.46,0:02:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,They know a lot about foreign lands, \Nand people say they're interesting folk.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.33,0:02:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But they're still very mysterious to us, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.97,0:02:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,They might try to lay their hands on the waterfall basin.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.98,0:02:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should we begrudge the wanderers some water?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.32,0:02:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not as if they're routing the water to rice fields like the villagers.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.61,0:02:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But I don't like outsiders coming in and out of there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.13,0:02:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Taku, our family's heir shouldn't \Nbe saying stingy things like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.03,0:02:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Just think of them as migratory birds.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.39,0:02:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Just let them do as they please.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.71,0:03:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, catch anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.86,0:03:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The fish can see you from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.23,0:03:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't take so many fish from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.03,0:03:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my family's mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.65,0:03:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you... the Guardian here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.90,0:03:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the owner's son.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.74,0:03:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.04,0:03:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Ohh... the son of the Guardian?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.21,0:03:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,"Then I'll give them back."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.61,0:03:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Or so I'd like to say, but we want something to eat, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.86,0:03:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you spare a fish per person?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.57,0:03:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess that would be okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.34,0:03:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.04,0:03:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll give the rest to the Guardian then.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.74,0:03:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Isaza of the {\i1}Watari.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.70,0:04:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be staying here again for a while.\NPleased to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.27,0:04:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure are a strange one, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.37,0:04:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,A son of the Guardian who's bad at fishing...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.19,0:04:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.78,0:04:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure caught a lot today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.07,0:04:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,How should I cook them?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.86,0:04:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What's with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.48,0:04:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's not always true that the son of the mountain's owner is good at fishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.25,0:04:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Wo woah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.37,0:04:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Looking closely, they're all over.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.83,0:04:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you liar.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.42,0:04:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard from my grandpa.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.26,0:04:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Your father isn't the Guardian of this mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.18,0:04:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a lie!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.97,0:04:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,My ancestors bought this land little by little.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.76,0:04:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Bought?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.57,0:05:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think that that makes\Nyou the Guardian of this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.33,0:05:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not a place with which\Npeople may do as they please.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.85,0:05:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not doing as we please.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.31,0:05:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a special mountain, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.61,0:05:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The land in this area is fertile because of this mountain,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.95,0:05:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,so my family has been protecting it all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.88,0:05:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,My father is the one who's preventing
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.40,0:05:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,everyone from damming that waterfall and routing it to the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.55,0:05:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you told by a mushi-shi to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.82,0:05:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I believe that was it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.47,0:05:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,My ancestors were told to do so by someone like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.40,0:05:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,They said that if we didn't, \Nthe mountain would become sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.94,0:05:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.48,0:05:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So this mountain is to you too...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.23,0:05:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well... it's okay then.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.65,0:05:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going to tell you to return the fish from yesterday. Sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.34,0:05:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Later then.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.73,0:05:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.62,0:06:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If you gave them to me because of some misunderstanding, I'll return them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.33,0:06:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no reason for me to take charity from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.66,0:06:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.61,0:06:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Just wait a little longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.93,0:06:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I already have today's catch, so it's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.64,0:06:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I said wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.32,0:06:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, what's this Guardian you guys are talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.04,0:06:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's that large catfish in this waterfall basin.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.57,0:06:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Who decided that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.65,0:06:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The mountain did.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.20,0:06:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who are to become Guardians are born with grass somewhere on their bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.19,0:06:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the marker.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.10,0:06:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I've seen him before. It's that large catfish with the grass on his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.88,0:06:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, I'm jealous.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.69,0:06:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Then have you seen the mist become colored and swell as if it were alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.35,0:06:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.06,0:07:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This area is the path of the light vein.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.87,0:07:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.69,0:07:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The source of life runs through this land.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.23,0:07:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It mixes with the water, evaporates, and becomes mist.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.67,0:07:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why the mist here has life.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.66,0:07:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why its color and shape change by day.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.33,0:07:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You can tell the condition of \Nthe land by looking at the mist.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.09,0:07:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.19,0:07:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Quickly, quickly! Don't panic!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.10,0:07:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.93,0:07:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm rather short, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.27,0:07:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,See you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.69,0:07:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you a lot of things I know, so next time, tell me something on your side.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.33,0:07:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know anything special.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.30,0:07:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Just anything ordinary is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.18,0:07:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I find the things happening \Nin the village to be interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.72,0:08:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, if it isn't the young master, Taku.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.18,0:08:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What's up? It's unlike you to come to the parlor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.24,0:08:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought that I might be able \Nto hear something interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.89,0:08:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You came at the right time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.82,0:08:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just telling the master about my travels.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.57,0:08:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, have a seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.56,0:08:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.49,0:08:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.68,0:08:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,My uncle's stories are always a bit exaggerated.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.45,0:08:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, and he also said he saw a strange kid in the town two mountains to the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.66,0:08:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,He was about ten and had white hair and green eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.50,0:08:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He was missing one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.14,0:08:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm? Who could he be? A foreigner?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.39,0:08:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He said it didn't seem like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.05,0:09:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm... two mountains to the south, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.01,0:09:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's in the path we take. \NI may be able to meet him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.71,0:09:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's right. The rainy season will end soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.51,0:09:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,When are you leaving?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.47,0:09:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.06,0:09:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,My grandpa looks at the mist\N every morning and decides.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.22,0:09:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.67,0:09:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,When it's bluish, the mountain's energy is silent, so we can move swiftly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.87,0:09:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,When it's reddish, it's the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.15,0:09:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,When it's golden, the mountain is in the best mood, so that's the best day to depart.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.71,0:09:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I see... How carefree it sounds...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.73,0:09:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you jealous?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.97,0:09:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,My future is already decided.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.76,0:09:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to live here and be concerned with the land just like my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.51,0:09:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm jealous.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.30,0:09:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.21,0:10:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,These maps show the movements \Nof the paths of the light vein.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.05,0:10:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Then I'll take this map.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.74,0:10:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.93,0:10:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Isaza, your information helped out a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.84,0:10:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm counting on you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.26,0:10:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.25,0:10:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how we make our living.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.93,0:10:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We sell information about mushi related rumors
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.04,0:10:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and the movements of the paths \Nof the light vein to mushi-shi.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.83,0:10:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,No one would feed us by just going around.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.90,0:10:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you should have said so in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.72,0:10:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, I would've gotten you that kind of story.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.30,0:10:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That wouldn't be good.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.83,0:10:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,If I don't know what's "normal" in the village,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.80,0:11:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't know what's unusual.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.61,0:11:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And also I like to hear about the village, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.27,0:11:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.81,0:11:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean, "Never mind"?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.33,0:11:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I got it already.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.55,0:11:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You're still sulking.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.38,0:11:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up. Don't follow me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.08,0:11:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.91,0:11:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,This is how I do things.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.59,0:11:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't ask you to apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.25,0:11:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Eep! It flashed!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.61,0:11:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if the rainy season will \Nbe over when this clears up...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.55,0:12:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.93,0:12:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Isaza?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.49,0:12:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It's golden!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.05,0:12:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The following year, they came around the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.05,0:12:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But it seemed the group consisted of \Ndifferent members than the year before.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.02,0:12:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we picked him up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.63,0:13:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That thing you told me turned out to be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.10,0:13:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We found him wandering about the town. He said he didn't have anywhere to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.02,0:13:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He looks strange, but he's a nice guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.96,0:13:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,His name is Ginko.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.73,0:13:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.10,0:13:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think he'll be with us for long, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.11,0:13:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He has a tendency to attract mushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.34,0:13:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be harmful to either him or the light vein if he stays around its path too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.79,0:13:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll likely be passed on to \Na mushi-shi in the near future.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.62,0:13:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Fumi, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.75,0:13:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Young master!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.90,0:13:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The master... the master has...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.76,0:13:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,As I said, it says in his will that the entire mountain will go to Taku.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.68,0:13:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Auntie, but even so...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.43,0:13:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Can he handle this all by himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.95,0:13:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The village has expanded so much \Nthat there's not enough water.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.82,0:14:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got to route the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.00,0:14:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If you leave it to us, we'll do a good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.23,0:14:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Taku...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.86,0:14:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Taku.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.42,0:14:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard from the mountain guards.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.22,0:14:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry about your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.18,0:14:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You haven't been coming to the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.11,0:14:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.02,0:14:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I... couldn't protect the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.75,0:14:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It was all taken up by my relatives.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.58,0:14:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon the waterfall will be dammed and the mountain will be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.21,0:14:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.43,0:15:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Taku, please listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.17,0:15:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something wrong with the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.22,0:15:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It won't calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.97,0:15:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The ground is hot and it smells strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.62,0:15:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The animals are also leaving and\N the light vein has begun to shift.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.51,0:15:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We too will move with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.07,0:15:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys be careful too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.42,0:15:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You aren't going to come here anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.79,0:15:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.37,0:15:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Say... Let me into your group.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.45,0:15:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I... don't want to stay here any longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.96,0:15:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Please take me, just like that guy Ginko.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.75,0:15:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I can see the colors of the mist too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.14,0:15:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't matter that I'm not real family, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.93,0:15:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,None of us are related by blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.89,0:15:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Grandpa decides who comes with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.01,0:16:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll ask him. Come to the fall tomorrow morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.54,0:16:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The mist is pure white.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.23,0:16:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There's definitely something wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.63,0:16:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This was never happened before.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.94,0:16:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's Isaza?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.27,0:16:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He left already.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.87,0:16:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You're lying! He...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.46,0:16:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be helped since the light vein began to move during the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.75,0:16:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Isaza asked me to tell you, "I'm sorry."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.07,0:17:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They cannot defy the light vein.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.14,0:17:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Watari{\i0} is a group where those who were kicked out from their villages due to mushi end up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.14,0:17:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're like that, you'll someday meet again.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.50,0:17:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean someone like you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.46,0:17:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you. It's time to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.14,0:17:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I was kicked out once again, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.65,0:17:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,He had something else to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.42,0:17:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, "You'd all better get away from here, too."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.86,0:17:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}From that day, the mountain's \Nmist was no longer colored.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.27,0:17:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Then half a year later...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.36,0:18:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The mountain spouted fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.51,0:18:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and those who had places to go, abandoned the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.15,0:18:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The mountain burned.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.72,0:18:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The waterfall dried up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.54,0:18:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But the fall basin remained as a marsh.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.29,0:18:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}One time, I saw the shadow of a large catfish.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.86,0:18:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But I could no longer see the crown of grass it once had on its head.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.01,0:18:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's been a decade and a few years. \NI've cleared the ash and planted trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.80,0:18:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The mountain recovered slowly, but without the richness that it used to have.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.91,0:18:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And many of our children were born weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.09,0:19:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Isaza and the others would probably know something.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.09,0:19:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It probably has something to do with the light vein.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.99,0:19:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But how do I save them?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.15,0:19:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I don't even know how to find \NIsaza and the others at this point.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.55,0:19:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The sound of footsteps on the grass on the mountain still makes me twitch...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.32,0:19:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}making me think that they may have come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.20,0:19:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Taku!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.98,0:19:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Taku, good news!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.57,0:19:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,There's someone at the lower house who says he can cure our children.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.94,0:19:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,All you have to do now is prepare \Nthe medicine as I showed you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.37,0:19:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and have him take it once a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.89,0:19:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You're...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.61,0:19:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,This land used to have the path of the light vein, but has since been abandoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.33,0:20:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Many mushi also moved with it,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.30,0:20:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,but those who stay close to people remained.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.48,0:20:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Could that be why our children are weak?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.14,0:20:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa... you seem to be quite knowledgeable about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.47,0:20:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys were born healthy with \Nthe benefit of the light vein,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.79,0:20:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,but your children weren't.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.98,0:20:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That medicine is mushi repellent \Nas well as nourishment.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.71,0:20:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll need it for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.09,0:20:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.57,0:20:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, you don't seem to remember, \Nbut I've met you before.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.71,0:20:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Sorry, I don't remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.29,0:20:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember Isaza?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.89,0:20:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Are you a friend of his?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.62,0:20:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,He's still an acquaintance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.86,0:20:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard about this place from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.61,0:20:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He said that you guys might need medicine about now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.05,0:21:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,He's doing the same as usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.22,0:21:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I see... Then it's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.08,0:21:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's fine as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.02,0:21:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,A large catfish and the shape of this marsh...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.76,0:21:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been here before, haven't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.10,0:21:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. It's him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.94,0:21:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He and the mountain have changed\N quite a bit, haven't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.14,0:21:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you agree...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.56,0:21:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Ex-Guardian?
